name: Juliana Rabbi - Remote Work Coach
content: Do women need to choose between a career and being a good mother?I know. Most people will say that, once you become a mother, you will never be able to prioritize your career again. You are "kind of done" with that.I disagree. ▪️ In case you are wondering, I'm not a mother. But I have close friends, clients and women around me who are mothers, and I want to share the perspective I heard from some of them about being a mother. ⚠️ Warning: this might change the way you approach being a mother and taking care of you careerA lot of mothers dream about a career that allows them to:✔️ Bring their young kids to school and pick them back✔️ Have lunch with them every day✔️Travel with the kids during the school holidays and work from there✔️ Spend time home when the kid got sick ✔️ Be able to spend more quality time with the kid, instead of arriving home from the office late and extremely tired, when the kid is about to go to bed🔘 Are those things even possible to happen?The answer is yes.🔹 When you have a remote job, you have more flexibility and autonomy to use your time as you wish.You can be an amazing and dedicated professional, and, at the same time,  a great mom who spends time with her family and enjoys it.🔸 I know things are more complex than that, but I want to bring your attention to the fact that working remotely will significantly increase the chances that you can keep improving your career after you have kids.The "traditional office life" is not kid friendly - and I'm sure you knew that already. What you may not know is that more and more moms are working remotely (or from home) and improving their life quality, spending more times with their kids and still being promoted.➡️ If you are a mother (or are planning to be one), and you also care about your career, I can help you to land a remote job.You will need to figure out a way to raise your kids and live life on your own terms...But I can help you to deal with the career part.⭐️ Send me a direct message and let's talk.#jobsearch #remotejobs #remotework #homeoffice #workfromhome

name: Laura Millán García
content: ¡Alejandro Mariana Muñoz y yo hemos tenido una idea! La hemos llamado “EL GRAN DESPERTAR DEL TALENT-BRAND” ⏰ ¿Te la cuento? 💥👇🙋🏻‍♂️ Alejandro es Talent Acquisition de Cabify, responsable desde hace varios años de la gestión de procesos de selección y atracción del mejor talento tecnológico en Cabify.🙋🏻‍♀️ Por mi parte, soy Brand Strategist de marcas y empresas: ideo, diseño y desarrollo estrategias de comunicación para generar un impacto real en las organizaciones y sus stakeholdersNos juntamos por casualidad leyéndonos en LinkedIn y hemos decidido sumar conocimientos para aportar nuestra visión sobre ciertos temas que pueden ser relevantes.💥💥💥 De esta fusión nace… El Gran Despertar del Talent-Brand: una sección conjunta de Employer Branding y Brand Strategy, en forma de artículos de LinkedIn, donde analizamos las tendencias, desafiamos las convenciones, conectamos los límites y damos espacio a la revolución que está redefiniendo la forma en que el talento y la marca se conectan.¿Te apetece? ¿Qué te parece? Nuestro primer artículo será sobre… La importancia de la marca personal de los empleados de tu empresa. 👉 Hablaremos sobre cómo la marca personal está cambiando las reglas del juego, y abriremos debate sobre si esto genera un conflicto de intereses o una simbiosis imprescindible para las empresas y sus trabajadores. 😎 ¡El próximo 24 de mayo estaremos de estreno! 😎#EmployerBranding #Branding #EstrategiaEmpresarial #EstrategiaDigital #Marca #Talento #ElGranDespertarDelTalentBrand

name: Álvaro García Lorenzo
content: El post llega unos días tarde (con algún que otro problema logístico de por medio). El viaje a Londres con los compañeros del Máster en gestión de empresas marítimo-portuarias y Derecho marítimo de la University of Deusto  ha sido una experiencia increíble. Antes de nada, quiero hablar sobre las dos visitas que tuvimos el día después de estar en la  International Maritime Organization y en el Lloyd's Register Así, tuvimos el placer de visitar el Britannia P&I Club, primer club de P&I del mundo y referente en el sector marítimo; además de la sede de International Oil Pollution Compensation Funds (IOPC Funds), vitales a la hora de mitigar los daños que pudiesen causar desastres debidos a la contaminación por hidrocarburos resultante de derrames de hidrocarburos persistentes de buques tanque.Gracias a sendas oportunidades, los conocimientos que hemos ido ganando a lo largo del curso se han visto reforzados y no podemos aguantar más las ganas de finalizar esta etapa y empezar a crecer dentro del sector marítimo.Con todo, me gustaría agradecer a mis compañeros por los magníficos momentos vividos, tanto en las visitas como en el tiempo de ocio del que disfrutamos (en algún que otro pub nos conocen ya de sobra). Finalmente, no podía olvidarme de Fernando. No se me ocurriría nadie mejor para poder compartir, disfrutar y aprender a la vez. Gracias infinitas por aguantarnos y estar a nuestro lado toda esta semana.#maritimeindustry #maritimelaw #pollution #oil #fidac #britannia #insurance #oportunidades #hidrocarburos #derecho #derechomaritimo #comerciointernacional #internationaltrade

name: Fiona L.
content: 𝗧𝗿𝘆𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗼 𝗳𝗶𝗻𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗻𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 𝗹𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝗺𝗶𝗻𝘂𝘁𝗲? 𝗛𝗲𝗿𝗲’𝘀 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝗜 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝗼𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗹/𝗠𝗮𝘆. (2022 edition!) Same time last year; I started my recruiting process, early February. I got offers at Asurion, Robinhood, Okta, NVIDIA and interviews at LinkedIn, Adobe, Corsair to name a few. Here were the steps that got me there:👩‍💻𝟭. 𝐔𝐩𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐮𝐦𝐞 (Wonsulting Template https://bit.ly/351yiy2)  Hiring managers focused on my leadership experiences and the impact I’ve made at various roles. I always input qualitative metrics on my all my projects, internships, and club experiences.Structure of bullets: what did you do, how did you accomplish it, and what were the results. 📌𝟮. 𝐌𝐚𝐤𝐞 𝐚 𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐚𝐩𝐩𝐥𝐲Out of hundreds of applications, it only takes 1 company to see your potential. However, you should expect to submit a substantial amount. I probably applied to 200+ total! 🧷use Simplify to auto fill your applications🧷network with professionals in the same team or role to gain insight on the product/potential project scope. (Either after you applied or land an interview) 👀𝟯. 𝐔𝐬𝐞 𝐨𝐫𝐠𝐚𝐧𝐢𝐳𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐬𝐨𝐟𝐭𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐞𝐬 𝐭𝐨 𝐤𝐞𝐞𝐩 𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐨𝐟 𝐚𝐩𝐩𝐥𝐢𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬I love Notion so much! It can be a tedious process but keep track of all companies that you submitted apps for. ✨Pro tip: I keep a list of recruiters and hiring managers emails regardless of my application status, just for future references and opportunities. As an incoming June 2023 graduate at University of California, Davis I’m still on the search for full time positions. Connect with me to share your current job search experiences! #intern #hiring #interview #internships #software #recruiters #linkedin #future #opportunities #rejection #linkedin #adobe

name: Pablo Sánchez Arias
content: Boost Your R Code's Performance with parSapply 🚀Hey LinkedIn fam! 👋 Are you looking to supercharge your R code and make it run faster? 🏃‍♂️ Today, I want to share with you an amazing function in R called parSapply that can significantly speed up your computations. 💨parSapply is a parallel computing function in R that allows you to distribute computations across multiple cores or processors, harnessing the power of parallel processing. 🚀 By using parSapply, you can take advantage of the full processing power of your machine, making your code more efficient and saving you precious time ⌛.Here's a simple example of how parSapply can be used to speed up your code:```R# Load the parallel packagelibrary(parallel)# Define a function to be applied in parallelmy_function <- function(x) { # Perform some computationally intensive task # ...}# Create a vector of inputsmy_data <- 1:100# Apply the function in parallel using parSapplyresults <- parSapply(my_data, my_function)```In this example, parSapply distributes the computations of the `my_function` across multiple cores, processing each element of `my_data` simultaneously. This can lead to a significant speedup compared to the sequential version of the code.By leveraging parallel processing with parSapply, you can tackle computationally intensive tasks more efficiently, such as large-scale simulations, data processing, or complex calculations. 💪So, if you find yourself working with large datasets or performing repetitive calculations in R, give parSapply a try! It's a powerful tool that can make a noticeable difference in your code's performance. ⚡️If you're interested in learning more about optimizing your R code and unlocking its full potential, I highly recommend checking out DataCamp's course "Writing Efficient R Code" (link: [https://lnkd.in/dVwBqbAN]). It covers various techniques and best practices to improve the efficiency and speed of your R code.Remember, in today's data-driven world, every second counts when it comes to data analysis and processing. Stay ahead of the game by optimizing your R code with parSapply and other performance-enhancing techniques. Happy coding! 💻✨#RProgramming #DataScience #ParallelProcessing #EfficientCoding #DataCamp
